	           <h4 style="text-align: left"><a href="http://vanfashionweek.com/">VANCOUVER FASHION WEEK</a></h4>

                <br/>   
                <h5 style="text-align: justify; line-height: 1.5; padding-right: 20px"> 
                <strong>What is it?</strong> <br/>
                <br/>
                Vancouver Fashion Week is a diverse and innovative bi-annual fashion experience that features both established and emerging designers. It is the fastest growing fashion week in the world and the only industry event that actively seeks out to showcase international award-winning designers from over 25 global fashion capitals. <br/>
                 <br/>
                <strong>What did I do?</strong> <br/>
                <br/>
                I am currently volunteering at VFW where I've mastered my Google and Facebook skills researching for new designers from Spain, Latin America and the US to join our event. My biggest achievement was in the South American region where I expanded the designer directory by 22% over 8 days. I secured 2 emerging designers (<a href="https://www.facebook.com/emmabelliniperu/">Emma Bellini</a> from Peru and <a href="https://www.facebook.com/florenciaocchiuzzi1818/?pnref=story">Florencia Occhiuzzi</a> from Uruguay) for the Fall/Winter 2016 season within a tight    deadline. <br/>
                 <BR/>
                I am the happiest person providing help to others so I assisted them in everything I could before, during and after the show. This involved flight tickets, hotel reservations, touristic recommendations and most importantly, moral support and a smile. As I went through the whole process with them, I established a meaningful relationship with them and their families. It didn’t end up there. I also supported and built connections with other Spanish speaker designers: <a href="http://www.ankurabrand.com/index.php/en/">Ankura</a>,  <a href="https://www.facebook.com/LAUTAROAMADEOTAMBUTTO/">LAT</a> and <a href="http://www.sousapitti.com">Sousa Pitti</a>. I was amazed with their creativity, energy and commitment to their careers. <br/>
                <br/>
                Moreover, I identified and developed new South American media partnerships which include <a href="http://revistablum.com/"> Revista Blum</a> (Peru),<a href="http://www.estilopunta.com/"> Estilo Punta</a> (Uruguay),<a href="http://www.dressmix.com.uy/"> DressMix</a> (Uruguay), <a href="http://www.ellas.pa/"> Ellas</a> (Panama) and<a href="http://www.quintatrends.com/"> Quinta Trends</a> (Chile).  I got these magazines to cover the event on their websites, social media channels and print issues. <br/>
                <br/>

