                <h5 style="text-align: justify; line-height: 1.5; padding-right: 20px"> 
                <strong>What is it?</strong> <br/>
                <br/>
                PurpleDirt is a collective of primarily female artists and organizers based in Nicaragua and Canada that believe fashion is a platform for social enrichment and women empowerment. The organization was created to support Nicaraguan artisans striving for an end to poverty in Nicaragua. It creates one-of-a-kind, expressive jewelry using upcycled materials from Canada and donate proceeds back into the community.  <br/>
                 <br/>
                <strong>What did I do?</strong> <br/>
                <br/>
                During my internship, I boosted the brand awareness by 30% by implementing a comprehensive social media strategy based on daily listening and engagement within the online community. It also included platform-specific posts and campaigns: fun-facts for <a href="https://twitter.com/shoppurpledirt"> Twitter</a>, video series for <a href="https://www.youtube.com/embed/zcD5i3Whdmk"> Youtube</a>, giveaway contests for <a href="https://www.facebook.com/ShopPurpleDirt/"> Facebook</a> and catchy images for <a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/qhSWwqF6fZ/?taken-by=shoppurpledirt"> Instagram</a>. Moreover, I amplified the content’s diversity and reach by monitoring and analyzing the social media activity of influencers and similar companies such as The Honest Company and Pura Vida Bracelets. <br/>
                <br/>
                My favourite part of working at PurpleDirt was creating a video series called "The Women of PurpleDirt" that allowed customers to create a connection with the artisans making their jewelry and build a long-lasting and meaningful relationship with the brand. I made the videos using Final Cut Pro X.
                <br/>
                </h5>

