               <h5 style="text-align: justify; line-height: 1.5; padding-right: 20px"> 
                <strong>What is it?</strong> <br/>
                <br/>
                ArtStarts in Schools is a not-for-profit organization that promotes art and creativity among British Columbia’s young people. Since 1996, ArtStarts has supported educators, artists, parents and students by offering a broad range of programs, services and resources to promote arts and creativity among British Columbia's young people.<br/>
                 <br/>
                <strong>What did I do?</strong> <br/>
                <br/>
                For 6 months now, I have been happily volunteering here. This position allows me to juggle multiple balls and exploit my imagination. I had the pleasure to be part of the <a href="http://artstarts.com/showcase"> Annual Showcase</a> by designing graphic material using Photoshop for the dinner which resulted in the increase of engagement of delegates. And, by catering for the two-day event with 100+ attendees which implied dealing with time constraints, specificity, and a fast-paced environment. <br/>
                <br/>
                During my weekly shift, I consistently and proactively communicate with the 9 team members via e-mail, phone and face-to-face, and help them with individual work plans that included but are not limited to data entry, gallery tours, exhibition set-up, research, paperwork, content curation and even poster runs. When I am attending the reception, I maximize the satisfaction of visitors by providing them with valuable information, solving their doubts, advocating for their interests and greeting them with the biggest smile. <br/>
                <br/>
                </h5>
